  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-08-13",
    "date": "2021-10-13T20:06:04Z",
    "text": "Parental Bereavement Act of 2021 or the Sarah Grace-Farley-Kluger Act\n\nThis bill entitles an eligible employee to up to 12 workweeks of leave during any 12-month period because of the death of a son or daughter.\n\n Such an employee may substitute any available paid leave for any leave without pay.\n\nThe bill applies the same leave entitlement to federal employees."
  },
